22
00:01:03.455 --> 00:01:08.485
is that they can trust you and that you're always there in case they need you.

23
00:01:08.485 --> 00:01:12.379
One of the tactics I've used with clients is to summarize

24
00:01:12.379 --> 00:01:16.415
the list of things they want because often clients are just sending random stuff to you.

25
00:01:16.415 --> 00:01:18.170
Oh I want this, I want this, I want this.

26
00:01:18.170 --> 00:01:21.395
What I like to do, summarize everything that they've

27
00:01:21.395 --> 00:01:25.415
said to me in the message stream of what they want or in another document,

28
00:01:25.415 --> 00:01:28.565
put it through, here is a checklist of what you want me to do.

29
00:01:28.565 --> 00:01:32.660
Then after that, go through and like I've done here,

30
00:01:32.660 --> 00:01:35.075
provide a summary of all the things I've done,

31
00:01:35.075 --> 00:01:38.750
checking them off and that communicates to the client, Oh, Okay.

32
00:01:38.750 --> 00:01:39.905
I know we're at now.

