00:01:39.905 --> 00:01:41.510
I know how much he's done.

34
00:01:41.510 --> 00:01:44.060
The one thing you don't want to do when you're working with

35
00:01:44.060 --> 00:01:46.670
clients on Upwork is get the job,

36
00:01:46.670 --> 00:01:49.415
do the work and don't communicate with them at all.

37
00:01:49.415 --> 00:01:51.510
You might think, okay. I'm doing a great job.

38
00:01:51.510 --> 00:01:53.780
I'm not bothering them. But you want to let

39
00:01:53.780 --> 00:01:56.705
them know how it's going throughout the process.

40
00:01:56.705 --> 00:01:59.480
Be responsive when they message you.

41
00:01:59.480 --> 00:02:03.830
Make sure to tell the client as soon as you've done something,

42
00:02:03.830 --> 00:02:05.515
give them regular updates.

43
00:02:05.515 --> 00:02:09.695
Obviously, you'll get a feel for the client's expectations over time.

44
00:02:09.695 --> 00:02:14.225
Some are quite needy and want daily or constant communication,

45
00:02:14.225 --> 00:02:17.915
others are happy with communication more spread out.

46
00:02:17.915 --> 00:02:20.585
But if you haven't heard from the client in a while,

47
00:02:20.585 --> 00:02:21.785
make sure to follow up.

48
00:02:21.785 --> 00:02:25.175
If you've done something new or need something else to go on with,

49
00:02:25.175 --> 00:02:26.510
make sure to follow up.

50
00:02:26.510 --> 00:02:30.800
It's on you to communicate as much as possible with the client

51
00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:35.110
and let them know that you're there and that you're actually working on their project.

52
00:02:35.110 --> 00:02:37.545
Again, remember here, I want to reiterate this,

53
00:02:37.545 --> 00:02:39.575
once you're on contract with a client,

54
00:02:39.575 --> 00:02:42.940
they have the ability to leave a review on your profile and that

55
00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:46.550
can be very detrimental if they give you a bad review.

56
00:02:46.550 --> 00:02:50.360
You want to make sure if you're on contract with a client,

57
00:02:50.360 --> 00:02:52.355
you not only do great work,

58
00:02:52.355 --> 00:02:54.800
but communicate well with them and make

59
00:02:54.800 --> 00:02:58.040
sure that if there's any issues whatsoever that they have,

60
00:02:58.040 --> 00:03:00.830
that they can bring it up with you and that you'll sort it out.

61
00:03:00.830 --> 00:03:05.255
That's a lot better than letting issues just sit around and then they

62
00:03:05.255 --> 00:03:09.840
won't communicate how they feel and suddenly you'll be getting a two,

63
00:03:09.840 --> 00:03:14.030
three star review at the end when you could have gotten a five-star review.

64
00:03:14.030 --> 00:03:18.000
What you need, especially when starting out, is five-star reviews.

65
00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:22.165
You want to make sure that every review you get on artwork is five-stars.

66
00:03:22.165 --> 00:03:23.550
Don't leave it up to chance,

67
00:03:23.550 --> 00:03:26.660
make sure that you're communicating constantly with the client,

68
00:03:26.660 --> 00:03:28.040
making sure that they're happy.

69
00:03:28.040 --> 00:03:32.365
One of the areas that I really like to communicate as well is around budget.

70
00:03:32.365 --> 00:03:35.835
A lot of clients on Upwork are budget conscious.

71
00:03:35.835 --> 00:03:38.960
If they ask you to do something that you think is

72
00:03:38.960 --> 00:03:41.749
going to take a long time and you're on an hourly contract,

73
00:03:41.749 --> 00:03:43.765
you don't want it to get to the point where,

74
00:03:43.765 --> 00:03:50.165
you do this 10 hour task and then it gets charged to them and they're like, "What?

75
00:03:50.165 --> 00:03:52.120
I didn't realize it was going to take that long."

76
00:03:52.120 --> 00:03:56.690
Even though you're in the right to do the work that they asked you,

77
00:03:56.690 --> 00:03:58.745
you want to communicate to them, "Okay.

78
00:03:58.745 --> 00:04:00.365
That's going to be time-consuming.

79
00:04:00.365 --> 00:04:02.600
It's going to take me around this many hours.

80
00:04:02.600 --> 00:04:04.055
As long as you're cool with that,

81
00:04:04.055 --> 00:04:06.300
otherwise, here are some other alternatives."

82
00:04:06.300 --> 00:04:09.395
You want to make sure that you're respecting their budget

83
00:04:09.395 --> 00:04:13.320
and you're not going to charge them more than they expect.

84
00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:16.775
Even if you've done the work and you're entitled to it,

85
00:04:16.775 --> 00:04:20.780
you want to know up front that the client is going to be happy with you doing that.

86
00:04:20.780 --> 00:04:23.480
One of the things I do when I'm communicating with

87
00:04:23.480 --> 00:04:27.680
clients is if they asked me to do something that's going to be very time consuming,

88
00:04:27.680 --> 00:04:30.870
I let them know that that's going to be time-consuming,

89
00:04:30.870 --> 00:04:33.335
here's a more cost effective way to do it.

90
00:04:33.335 --> 00:04:35.855
Clients often will really appreciate it.

91
00:04:35.855 --> 00:04:37.520
If they say, "Look, that's cool,

92
00:04:37.520 --> 00:04:38.855
I want you to still do it."

93
00:04:38.855 --> 00:04:40.835
That's fine, you've done all you can.

94
00:04:40.835 --> 00:04:45.740
But that's a little extra step that I like to take when communicating with clients.

95
00:04:45.740 --> 00:04:47.180
Also during this process,

96
00:04:47.180 --> 00:04:49.865
you want to keep in mind that this could be a repeat customer

97
00:04:49.865 --> 00:04:53.120
and you could actually build a long-term relationship with them.

98
00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:57.725
If that's the case, I would recommend getting on the phone with them every now and then,

99
00:04:57.725 --> 00:05:01.505
maybe meeting up with them if they are in the same city as you.

100
00:05:01.505 --> 00:05:04.610
Try and build a relationship with them because

101
00:05:04.610 --> 00:05:08.030
clients like to come back to the same freelancers again and again.

102
00:05:08.030 --> 00:05:10.340
It's hard to find good people.

103
00:05:10.340 --> 00:05:11.640
As a business owner,

104
00:05:11.640 --> 00:05:15.205
I've outsourced once before and it was a terrible experience.

105
00:05:15.205 --> 00:05:19.835
The freelancer just couldn't figure out even a basic task.

106
00:05:19.835 --> 00:05:23.570
This is the environment that clients are working with.

107
00:05:23.570 --> 00:05:29.345
That's where trust and relationship become so important to you and the client.

108
00:05:29.345 --> 00:05:31.535
You want to make sure that if

109
00:05:31.535 --> 00:05:34.430
you trying to build a long-term relationship with these clients,

110
00:05:34.430 --> 00:05:36.035
which you ideally should be,

111
00:05:36.035 --> 00:05:38.750
that you communicate with them in as many ways.

112
00:05:38.750 --> 00:05:40.790
That's going to communicate, trust,

113
00:05:40.790 --> 00:05:43.840
familiarity, and build a relationship with them.

114
00:05:43.840 --> 00:05:45.080
Get them on the phone,

115
00:05:45.080 --> 00:05:46.715
meet them in person if you can,

116
00:05:46.715 --> 00:05:48.935
and build the relationship that way.

117
00:05:48.935 --> 00:05:50.930
Again, we talked about this in the last video,

